OL,3,CMan, 24, with terminal brain tumour
OL,4,Cjoins calls for more research
OL,6,F"It was shock and I just put my head
OL,7,Fin my hands. I wasn't crying or
OL,8,Fanything - just completely overwhelmed
OL,9,Fby the news", he said.
OL,11,F"It was an absolutely shocking
OL,12,Frevelation to me.
OL,14,F"I was very worried - very naturally -
OL,15,Fanxious and scared about my future."
OL,17,FHis condition means he's at risk of
OL,18,Fseizures and he now undergoes regular
OL,19,Fchemotherapy and radiotherapy to
OL,20,Fprolong his life.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/6
